resources NI(20),SW(40)
notes
We will conduct Reimei-ESR coordinated observations 
to investigate fine-scale auroral height distribution 
and ion upflows. These observations are also run as 
simultaneous observations between ESR and auroral radio 
emissions in MF range.

We will run the sweep observational mode with taro 
pulse code.
- Geomagnetic meridian scan with 32m dish (1 scan: 2-min).
- Record ESR 42m data simultaneously.

(PIs: Dr. T. Sakanoi, Prof. T. Ono, and Dr. S. C. Buchert)

